                             SPELLING UTILITY
                             ================

One for the kids! Follow the loading instructions and Tutorial below and 
you'll soon get the hang of it.

LOADING INSTRUCTIONS - Low Resolution only.
====================

1. Switch on/Reset with this disc in the drive.
2. Double-click on SPELL.PRG.
3. Loading takes about 10 - 15 seconds.

TUTORIAL - Use the Left Mouse Button only.
========

1. Click on the START button.
   A picture will scroll down into the (yellow) box, and a number of 
   dashes (as many as there are letters in the word) will appear in 
   the (green) answer box. 

2. Click on a letter on the (red) keyboard. It will appear in the answer 
   box. Now click on the key marked with a bell. The letter will be 
   removed from the anwer box. This is how to correct mistakes
   (clangers).

3. Enter your full answer by clicking on the letters on the  keyboard.
   Now click on the key marked with three horizontal lines. You will
   see the correct answer appear over the picture, and a tick or cross
   appear in the scorebox. Another picture will then scroll down.

4. Click on the black arrow to the left of the picture. The previous
   picture will scroll back into view. Click on the arrow to the 
   right of the picture, and the new picture scrolls down again. So,
   you can scroll the piccies until you find one you can spell, or
   retry one you got wrong.

5. Click on the START button again, then click on YES in the prompt box.
   The SELECT GRADE etc message will appear in the picture box. Now click
   on the word TRICKY at the bottom of the picture box.The highlight will
   move from EASY to TRICKY, meaning you have selected the TRICKY grade
   of words/pictures.
   Now click on the key marked with a vertical arrow. The case of the
   keyboard letters will change. Click on the arrow key again to change
   it back.
   Finally click on the START button and off you go again. The Grade and
   letter case cannot be changed once you start spelling words,but you
   can (re)START at any time.

6. To finish using the utility, click on the STOP button, then click on
   YES in the prompt box. You will be returned to the Desktop.

7. Eerrrrr - Thats it.

      There are sixteen pictures/words to a Grade,and they are always
      presented in a random order to slow up rote learning. The Grades
      should be suitable for six - ten year olds. Enjoy!

